Date: 16 May 2005
From: ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>
Source: Jakarta Post [edited]
<http://www.alertnet.org/thenews/newsdesk/JAK54025.htm>

More children tested for polio
-------------------------------
Bogor Health Agency is testing feces and urine [poliovirus is excreted in
feces - Mod.MPP] samples of 5 children believed to have contracted polio
amid the recent outbreak in the country.
Agency head Djono Karjoeki said on Sunday [15 May 2005] that the agency had
previously tested 3 other children, and the results were negative.
Djono said around 101 health centers in the regency were scheduled to carry
out a massive immunization program on March 31 [presumably a typo in the
newswire, and the date should be 31 May 2005. - Mod.MPP]
There have been at least 8 cases of polio as of 14 May [2005], all coming
from villages near the West Java town of Sukabumi. One of them is being
treated in Jakarta.
